		  	 <table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF BLINDING SPEED</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Rogue</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;58</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;15 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;30 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;28 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline the rogue will be hasted (e.g. will hit much faster).  This haste stacks with every other haste in the game including haste items and spells.  This discipline lasts for 15 seconds and has a base reuse time of 30 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the rogue gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>BLINKO 45TH SEASON OF POVAR</span><b>, By Blinko</b><br><br>All I know is that if this stacks with all other haste items and spells and (im not sure) but MAY reduce or rid you of the haste speed cap then you can bring your deley so low that you have a 2.0 ratio and turn into a killing machine.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>MINIMUM DELAY CAP</span><b>, By Andre</b><br><br>I'm not sure what the minimum delay cap is supposed to be set at anymore (I once knew from reading 2nd hand posts about it), but <p>I was one of the lucky few who was able to use a scourgetail whip.  This had a 5 delay 30 dmg.  With SLTW, I could take any spiroc except lightbringer out without it getting in one hit.  In extraordinary circumstances, they would hit me once and sometimes twice.
<p>Without SLTW, I would get hit a maximum of 10 times in a fight against normal spirocs, excepting warriors and the lightbringer.  I have heard about this minimum delay cap, and I think after experiencing the whip with and without SLTW, that perhaps there might be no delay cap.
<p>I know this has been tested, but from my experience, I believe those tests might not be reliable for all situations.
Its just something to consider when considering these disciplines.

<p>andre, 53rd ranger<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WORTHLESS?</span><b>, By Kawless</b><br><br>Now THIS could be a useless skill, since there's a damn good chance you've already reached the minimum delay cap.
<br><hr size='1'></td>
